You are a Senior Clinical UX Architect and Healthcare Information Designer.

Review the Atlas Health Medical Protocol Detail page and perform a complete Information Architecture audit.

Do NOT change any functionality, calculations, workflows, permissions, APIs, database structures, backend logic, or business rules.

Your objective is to eliminate redundant information and enforce a strict Single Source of Truth model throughout the interface.

--------------------------------------------------

PROBLEM TO SOLVE
--------------------------------------------------

The Protocol Header already displays core protocol metadata:

• Status
• Duration
• Number of Phases
• Number of Compounds
• Evidence Level
• Category
• Complexity

However, the same information is repeated inside tabs and side panels.

This creates:

• Visual clutter
• Cognitive overload
• Wasted screen space
• Reduced physician confidence
• Risk of inconsistent values
• Poor information hierarchy

A physician should never see the same protocol metadata twice on the same screen.

--------------------------------------------------

SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH RULE
--------------------------------------------------

Protocol metadata must be displayed only once.

The Protocol Header becomes the authoritative source for:

• Protocol Name
• Status
• Category
• Complexity
• Duration
• Number of Phases
• Number of Compounds
• Evidence Level

No other section may repeat these values.

All sections must read from the same protocol object.

Example:

protocol.durationWeeks
protocol.phaseCount
protocol.compoundCount
protocol.category
protocol.complexity
protocol.evidenceLevel

Never duplicate state.

Never hardcode values.

Never create local copies.

